The Osun State Governor, Gboyega Oyetola, has approved the implementation of N30,000 minimum wage for workers in Osun State. Annual salary increment, lifting of embargo on promotion and conversion have all been approved. The governor said that the implementation takes effect from November 1. He made this known in a tweet on Friday. “Governor Oyetola approves New Minimum Wage for workers with effect from November 1, Annual Salary Increment, Embargo on Promotion and Conversion lifted,” he tweeted.